PacStats: Statistical charts about Archlinux pacman activity
Copyright (C) 2010 Angelo "Encelo" Theodorou <encelo@gmail.com>

http://pacstats.googlecode.com

Info
----
PacStats parses pacman.log and the pacman lib directory to make this information 
available to statistical chart plugins.

Dependencies
------------
Python (Program)
GTK2, PyGTK, Libglade (GUI)
SQLite, PySQLite if Python <= 2.4 (DB)
MatPlotLib, NumPy (Statistical charts)
Epydoc and Graphviz (Docs generation)

Please note that, even if using GtkBuilder, at the moment libglade is still 
needed for correct localization of the GUI.

Installation
------------
To install the program, type:
	$ python setup.py install [ --root=path --prefix=path ]

You can specify a prefix (e.g. /usr) and an alternative root (e.g. /mnt/hdb1).

Generating Docs
---------------
To generate automatic documentation type:
	$ epydoc -o epydoc --name=pacstats --url=http://pacstats.googlecode.com --graph=all PacStats/*.py PacStats/charts/*.py
